longBusinessSummary: Gold Rock Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, develops techniques, products, and services for consumption worldwide. It focuses on the certification of the patented Z MIX material and the subsequent use of Z MIX in construction of large scale housing developments. The company also engages in the business of international forest management, including harvesting damaged forest areas and replanting with a hybrid tree. It is also involved in building wind turbines, the management of power plants, wood processing, reforestation, and construction projects. In addition, the company engages in the production, generation, transmission, and sale of electricity through power plants on tribal/Indian lands. Further, it designs, produces, and sells wind turbine equipment worldwide. The company was formerly known as Composite Holdings, Inc. and changed its name to Gold Rock Holdings, Inc. in September 2004. Gold Rock Holdings, Inc. was founded in 1993 and is based in Las Vegas, Nevada.
